cyclone.name: ELSA
cyclone.current_location: about 30 mi E of Havana, Cuba and 115 mi S of Key West, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: continuing northwest then turning north-northwest toward the Florida Keys and the west coast of Florida, then curving north-northeast up the U.S. Southeast coast
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Big Bend coast near Cedar Key

weather_observation.watch_coast: West of the Ochlockonee River to Indian Pass, Florida (Tropical Storm Watch)
weather_observation.warning_coast: Florida Keys from Craig Key to Dry Tortugas and west coast of Florida from Flamingo to Ochlockonee River (Tropical Storm Warning); Bonita Beach to Aucilla River including Tampa Bay (Storm-Surge Warning)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Central and western Cuba, Florida Keys, Florida west coast, Florida Big Bend, then coastal Georgia and the Carolinas
